Highlife is a music genre that started in West Africa in coastal cities of present day Ghana in the 19th century. Highlife is a local fusion of African beats and western jazz melodies.
Hiplife is a Ghanaian musical genre that fuses Ghanaian language, Ghanaian culture and hip hop. Hiplife is mostly recorded in the Akan language.
